name: Ragnar Trail Los Coyotes - CA
intro:
Caw, caw… caw, caw. Do you hear that sound, young Ragnarian? Yes, it’s the call for adventure. Our brand new Southern California trail race, Ragnar Trail Los Coyotes-CA presented by Salomon, is located about an hour and a half outside of San Diego in the Native American Indian Reservation known as Los Coyotes. The trails at Los Coyotes Reservation will bring you on a spiritual journey, into an alpine wonderland of junipers, pines, and oaks, and to mountaintops where you will experience views of the Anza-Borrego Desert to the East and layers of beautiful mountain ranges to the West. All three trails start and stop at Ragnar Village where you can expect camping, s’mores, a bonfire and billions of stars overhead. Rally your team of 8 (or 4) members and enjoy the WILD air, call out to your spirit animal and find what makes you feel young, spirited and free.

Ragnar Trail Los Coyotes-CA is part of the Double Medal Series. Triple your bling in 2016 by running Reebok Ragnar So Cal and Ragnar Trail Los Coyotes-CA and earn yourself the highly exclusive Southern Ragnar Republic medal!

Any Captain who signs up for Ragnar Trail Los Coyotes is guaranteed to be selected during the 2017 Reebok Ragnar SoCal lottery. Los Coyotes Captain’s will still need to register for the SoCal lottery, but their team is guaranteed to be chosen.

**Guaranteed entry to So Cal is not available for teams who transfer out of Los Coyotes.
home:
Ragnar Trail Vail Lake – CA, presented by Salomon, will be held November 11-12, 2016. Teams will conquer a trifecta of beautiful Southern California trails at this overnight running adventure. With large shady oaks, abundant wildlife, and scenic views of the shimmering lake, it doesn’t get much better!

Vail Lake Resort may only be 7 miles from I-15, nestled neatly in between Los Angeles and San Diego, but you’ll feel like you are on another planet. Vail Lake is secluded from the congestion of Southern California and borders Cleveland National Forest, Agua Tibia Wilderness, and BLM Land. With miles of exquisite trail running terrain, teams will conquer the course under the stars this Fall!

 
 
 We are proud to announce that Vail Lake is a certified sustainable event.
 
 
 
 
 
 

The Child Abuse Prevention Center is the county’s leading not-for-profit organization focused exclusively on the prevention of child abuse. The center’s early intervention programs have a well-documented record of strengthening and improving parent-child relationships, working to prevent child abuse before it occurs. Our goals are accomplished by matching families at risk of child abuse with professional caseworkers who work with them directly in their homes. The goal of intervention is to replace parenting patterns that may lead to abuse and neglect with nurturing parenting styles, as well as to empower parents to become self-sufficient. The Child Abuse Prevention Center is a 501(c)3 tax exempt entity, the fourth largest not-for-profit dedicated to the prevention of child abuse in the country and one of 100 centers nationwide sponsored in part by the National Exchange Club Foundation for the Prevention of Child Abuse. More information can be found here: www.BrightFutures4kids.org

 

We love our military!

If at least half of your team is made up of service members you qualify for a $100 military discount! Ragnar offers flexible team transfer options and policy for last-minute deployments. Call or email customer service for details. 801.499.5024/ customerservice@ragnarrelay.com
village:
Ragnar Village is the heart and soul of the event. Each trail begins and ends in Ragnar Village. It is the start line, the finish line, and the exchange point. After each loop you will return to the support of your teammates and the adulation of the teams around you. Ragnar Village will be complete with:

  • Bonfire, s'mores, coffee, hot chocolate
  • Food and Snacks - 1 FREE Meal per participant (Friday night dinner from Food Trucks). Breakfast and lunch available for purchase from Food Trucks.
    • Friday Breakfast - Marcel Belgiun Waffles
    • Friday Lunch - Organic Food Truck and Mangia Mangia
    • Friday Dinner - Organic Food Truck, Mangia Mangia, Epic Eatz, Super Q, Seoulman Korean BBQ, Freak Brothers Pizza
    • Saturday Breakfast - Marcel Belgiun Waffles, Epic Eatz
    • Saturday Lunch - Mangia Mangia and Seoulman Korean BBQ
  • Freak Brothers Pizza available 24hrs!
  • Atlas Wine sales! $1 from each glass goes to FACESS charity! 
  • Games and Giveaways
  • Ragnar Swag available at the Merch Tent
  • Yoga Sessions by Mountain Sky Yoga Instructor - Bring your own Mat
  • Movies
  • Billions of stars

Team Campsite

Each team may choose where to set up their team campsite in the camping area. Teams will be allowed to drive up to the camping area and unload their gear. Awards will be given for the best decorated team campsite and almost anything goes: tents, canopies, camping chairs, BBQ's, kiddie pools full of Kool-Aid, whatever.

ClickCamp- Skip the packing stress. Come to Ragnar in a relaxed way, without your tent. A Click Camp tent, sleeping bag, air mattress, cot, and chairs are waiting for you. You just show up and focus on the important things: your team and the race.

meta_description: Our brand new Southern California trail race, Ragnar Trail Los Coyotes-CA presented by Salomon, is located about an hour and a half outside of San Diego in the Native American Indian Reservation known as Los Coyotes. The trails at Los Coyotes Reservation will bring you on a spiritual journey, into an alpine wonderland of junipers, pines, and oaks, and to mountaintops where you will experience views of the Anza-Borrego Desert to the East and the Pacific Ocean to the West.

legs.name: Green Loop - Dead Cow Trail
legs.description: Take solace knowing that the name of the loop comes from the name of one of the roads on which we run, not the way you will feel afterwards. This loop is fun and challenging. After looping around past the Transition Tent, Green runs through the camping area with Yellow and Red. After a quarter-mile, Yellow and Red turn left for a hard slog uphill. Don’t smile too big, your climb is to come. The next half-mile is a gentle climb up a grassy double-track, the oaks of the Village slowly giving way to more big pines. At this point the loop crosses Yellow and jumps onto a well graded dirt road to continue the climb. You can do it, breath through the burn for one mile, each step bringing a more spectacular view of the valley below. At mile two you will feel the reward of your efforts with a right turn onto the Dead Cow double-track road. This road is just rough enough and has the perfect downhill pitch that makes it feel like a fast fun single-track. You will grin as you wind down and around granite outcroppings, big pines, and strands of old oaks. At mile 3 Dead Cow spits you back onto the well graded dirt road and joins you with the Yellow for a race back through the campground and under the Ragnar arch.

legs.name: Yellow - San Ysidro Creek
legs.description: The Yellow Loop leaves Ragnar Village with Green and Red and cuts through the heart of the camping area under a canopy of huge oaks. At a quarter-mile, Green splits off right and you continue up a well graded dirt road. The pitch is gradual at first while the tree canopy gives way to views of the ridgelines above but near mile one, the tough get going and the rest of us start power hiking, as the next half mile is pretty steep. Just past mile one comes your sweet relief. The Red Loop soldiers on up the road while you bank right onto a fast single-track that plunges you back down into the tree cover. Run with care as there are some short technical sections before a short bridge crossing San Ysidro Creek, which runs dry most of the time. After the bridge there is a short steep climb up a near vertical wall which gains an open ridgeline with tremendous views of the valley below. The next mile is a fast and furious single-track decent back to the valley floor where you cross the outbound Green Loop and then turn right to join the end of the Green Loop back to Ragnar Village.

legs.name: Red Loop - Hot Springs Mountain Trail
legs.description: Weighing in at 7.9 miles and 1752’ of gain, the Red Loop is a beautiful challenge. The views from the ridgetops and the twists and turns of running in creekbeds make this loop a Ragnar staff favorite. The first three-quarters of a mile are tame enough, leaving Green behind early and continuing with Yellow on a dirt road. But then the volume gets turned up on your screaming quads. When Yellow splits away to your right, you have half a mile more of burn. Then a left takes you off the road and onto a single-track down a dry creekbed, twisting and winding through granite boulders, then up and over ridgelines with some kick butt views before dropping you back to the creekbed. Remember what we promised…beautiful challenge. At mile 3.5 the trail pops you out to Hot Springs Mountain Road and a Ragnar water station (remember we are cupless). The next mile and a half will be your fastest on the course. Hot Springs Mountain Road is a steep downhill graded dirt road, so get in the zone and hammer. Near mile 5 a sharp left takes you down some switchbacks and onto a single-track that roughly hugs a contour for a mile to bend you back up canyon. The final stretch takes you across a couple of road crossings and then up a gradual climb on a dirt road that brings you back to the cheers of your teammates.

travel.content:
Directions

Ragnar Trail Los Coyotes is located at Los Coyotes Indian Reservation located at 2300 Camino San Ignacio Rd in Warner Springs, CA 92086. See Map of Reservation.

 

NO Cell Service 

There is no cell service at the venue. Only at the top of the red and yellow loops. 

 

Parking Fee - Prepurchase Passes

Parking Passes will be available on site for $15 per vehicle per day, CASH ONLY. 

Please plan ahead and carpool! Fee will be collected by staff upon arrival. There will be a parking fee of $30 per RV/TRAILER, PER DAY. Cash Only. 

 

Parking & Gear Drop

Thursday and Friday Arrival: When you arrive at Los Coyotes Indian Reservation you will follow signs and volunteer directions to the drop off zones located in the camping areas. Teams will be able to drop off their gear in designated areas close to the camping areas. This will be very similar to the airport loading and unloading zone. You will unload all of your gear, QUICKLY, and go find a campsite. Drivers will stay with the vehicle while the team and gear are unloaded. The driver will then follow signs to the parking area a 1/4 mile down the road and walk back to the camping area. No vehicles will be allowed to park at the event area with the exception of volunteers arriving after shuttle hours.

  • Thursday arrival is between 4pm and 12am NO EXCEPTIONS. You will not be admitted entry outside of these hours.
  • Volunteers  staying temporarily for their shift will be able to park in our designated volunteer parking area close to the village and will need to remove their car as soon as their shift is finished. Any volunteers staying for the entire event can follow the same procedure as the teams.

Saturday Departure: Drivers will walk out to the parking area. They will drive back to the camping area in their own vehicles and pick up their team (who should be prepared and waiting) and gear at the designated pick up locations, QUICKLY, and head on home!

All teams must leave the venue by 6:30 p.m. on Saturday.

 

RV's and Trailers will be allowed at the event. No reservation necessary. There will not be any hookups available. There will be a parking fee of $30 per RV/TRAILER, PER DAY. Cash Only. 

No hook-ups will be available. RV area will be about a 5 minute walk to the main event area.

 

Camping

Camping Thursday and Friday nights in the Ragnar Village is included in your registration fee. This includes camping for all of your team and support crew(family & friends). Teams may select their campsite upon arrival (first come, first served). Campsites will be marked off to 300 square feet (17X17) per team. There is no need to contact Los Coyotes Indian Reservation for campsite accommodations for Thursday and Friday nights.

  • Vehicles will be allowed in the village for a speedy drop of so make sure everything is packed in bags and ready to be unloaded. Awards will be given for the best decorated team campsite and almost anything goes: tents, canopies, couches, camping chairs, BBQ’s, kiddie pools full of Kool-Aid, whatever.

  • Packing List - What should you pack? Check out the Ragnar Trail Ultimate Packing Guide.  It will be very cold at night. Pack warm clothes and camping gear. It also gets dusty so pack a buff and gators.

  • If you don't have all the camping gear, or don't want to worry about it.. check out Click Camp. They set up and clean up for you- all you need to bring are your running clothes and shoes! 

Click Camp

How it works- It's just like a hotel. All you have to do is reserve your tent, check-in with our on site hosts, and then check out. 

When you arrive on-site Click Camp will have a private area where you are greeted by one of our hosts. The hosts will quickly confirm your reservation then walk you to your tent accommodations. To make your return trip to your tent easier we have identified your tent with a small placard.

When you finish running your race make your way back to your tent and we will help you with check out when you're ready. 

With Click Camp there is no clean-up, no storing, no wondering where you'll sleep, and most importantly a good night's rest so you can run your best race. 

 

Elevated Legs Rental

Turn your campsite into a recovery station! Our partners Elevated Legs are renting legs for $120 for the whole race - that's $15/person for a team of 8! Don’t forget that you will need a power source. We highly recommend the Goal Zero Yetis.

For more information check out: http://elevatedlegs.com/rent/ragnar/

*Be sure to rent your legs before Monday, November 7th to ensure delivery before the race!*

reg_system.name: Ragnar Trail Los Coyotes - CA
reg_system.description: Caw, caw… caw, caw. Do you hear that sound, young Ragnarian? Yes, it’s the call for adventure. Our brand new Southern California trail race, Ragnar Trail Los Coyotes-CA presented by Salomon, is located about an hour and a half outside of San Diego in the Native American Indian Reservation known as Los Coyotes. The tribe of Native Americans have called this place home since the 1800s, and now you, and your tribe will get to experience the magic of this native land. The trails at Los Coyotes Reservation will bring you on a spiritual journey, into a high desert land filled with Joshua trees, and to the tops of foothills where you’ll experience views of the Anza-Borrego Desert to the East and the Pacific Ocean to the West. All three trails start and stop at Ragnar Village where you can expect camping, s’mores, a bonfire and billions of stars overhead. This overnight trail running journey isn’t an easy one, but no transformative experience ever is. Rally your team of 8 (or 4) members and dance around the fire, put on war paint, call out to your spirit animal and find your #innerWILD.
